<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,534,986]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,351,573,599]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Description.</emphasis>
The colony is 
<quantity box="[521,593,573,599]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="cm" value="22.0">22 cm</quantity>
wide and 
<quantity box="[712,783,573,599]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="cm" value="11.0">11 cm</quantity>
high, and a holdfast is present (
<figureCitation box="[1151,1222,573,599]" captionStart="FIGURE 7. a" captionStartId="13.[151,255,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[175,1418,197,1952]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[175,1419,197,1953]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. a, RMNH Coel. 38768, holotype of Astrogorgia fruticosa n. sp.; b, RMNH Coel. 38769, Echinogorgia sp. a; c, RMNH Coel. 38770, Echinogorgia sp. b; d, RMNH Coel. 38771, Echinogorgia sp. b. Scales 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186750/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number box="[1206,1222,573,599]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Branching is in one plane, anastomoses are frequent, forming a network. Polyps are situated all around the branches, the calyces are low, dome-shaped.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,534,986]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Polyps are retracted, with a collaret and points formed from flattened spindles, up to 
<quantity box="[1203,1308,689,715]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.20 mm</quantity>
long, with sparse tuberculation (
<figureCitation box="[402,473,728,754]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,194,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[172,1416,194,1950]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. RMNH Coel. 38769, Echinogorgia sp. a: a polyp spindles; b, spindles of interior; c, thornscales of surface layer; d, capstan derivatives of the subsurface layer." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186752/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number box="[457,473,728,754]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
a). The point spindles have one end slightly dentate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,534,986]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Surface layer of the coenenchyme has thornscales, up to 
<quantity box="[887,994,766,792]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.40 mm</quantity>
long; additionally a few unilaterally spinose spindles are present (
<figureCitation box="[499,583,805,831]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,194,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[172,1416,194,1950]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. RMNH Coel. 38769, Echinogorgia sp. a: a polyp spindles; b, spindles of interior; c, thornscales of surface layer; d, capstan derivatives of the subsurface layer." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186752/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Figs. 
<number box="[567,583,805,831]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
c, 
<number box="[610,640,805,831]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="10.0">10</number>
a–b). The inner layer has spindles, up to 
<quantity box="[1127,1233,805,831]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.40 mm</quantity>
long, many with one or two side branches (
<figureCitation box="[471,550,844,870]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,194,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[172,1416,194,1950]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. RMNH Coel. 38769, Echinogorgia sp. a: a polyp spindles; b, spindles of interior; c, thornscales of surface layer; d, capstan derivatives of the subsurface layer." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186752/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Figs 
<number box="[534,550,844,870]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
b, 
<number box="[580,613,844,870]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="10.0">10</number>
c). Furthermore, small derivatives of capstans are present; length of these sclerites up to 
<quantity box="[388,492,882,908]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.10 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[509,579,882,908]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,194,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[172,1416,194,1950]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. RMNH Coel. 38769, Echinogorgia sp. a: a polyp spindles; b, spindles of interior; c, thornscales of surface layer; d, capstan derivatives of the subsurface layer." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186752/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number box="[563,579,882,908]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
d).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,534,986]" box="[197,1299,920,947]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,289,920,946]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Colour.</emphasis>
Alive, the colony was purple in colour, preserved it is brown. Sclerites are colourless.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,1339,959,986]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
